The paper discusses the role of social media in human behavior, specifically in the context of online information consumption and production. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including social computing (cs.SOC), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Additionally, the paper reports on a large-scale experiment, which involves data analysis and statistical modeling, making it relevant to the sub-category of social informatics (cs.SI).
